    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Durable Execution Value — Cloud only",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 11,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "\nAnswers three business-level questions with only the customer-visible `temporal_cloud_v1_*`\nOpenMetrics — no internal-analytics-sourced data:\n\n1. **Are my business processes succeeding?** Workflow and Activity success rates, globally and\n   per-namespace.\n2. **Is Temporal helping where it otherwise couldn't?** Activity retries absorbed — attempts that\n   failed but were retried and eventually succeeded — compared against successful workflows.\n3. **How long are my business processes taking?** Workflow schedule-to-close latency by workflow type.\n\n> **Derivation — Activity retries absorbed.** `temporal_cloud_v1_activity_fail_count` counts only\n> *final* Activity failures (all retries exhausted); `temporal_cloud_v1_activity_task_fail_count`\n> counts *every failed attempt*, including ones later retried into a success. The difference between\n> the two is exactly \"attempts that failed but Temporal retried through\" — retries absorbed.\n>\n> **Caveat — the \"success rate without retries\" and \"9's gained\" panels are approximations, not\n> exact.** They model each absorbed retry as if it would have caused one additional Workflow\n> failure, which isn't precisely true (a Workflow can have many Activities/retries, or recover via\n> other paths). Treat them as a rough, directionally-correct story, the same caveat Temporal's own\n> team gives when walking through this analysis internally.\n>\n> **What this can't measure.** None of this captures the value of Workflow-level crash protection —\n> Temporal recovering a Workflow after a Worker/process crash, as opposed to a single Activity\n> failing while the process stays up. That's a materially bigger reliability story with no\n> corresponding OpenMetrics counter today (Workflow Task retries reflect Sticky-cache evictions too,\n> not just crashes, so they're not a clean proxy either).\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Are My Business Processes Succeeding? — Workflow Completion / Activity Result",
      "collapsed": false,
